		<m:mi> m </m:mi>
		<m:mo> / </m:mo>
		<m:msup>
			<m:mi> s </m:mi>
			<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
		</m:msup>
	</m:math>. For the sake of convenience, we consider acceleration due to gravity is equal to 10 
<m:math>
		<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
		<m:mi> m </m:mi>
		<m:mo> / </m:mo>
		<m:msup>
			<m:mi> s </m:mi>
			<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
		</m:msup>
	</m:math>. Here, we have taken numerical values so that we have the feel of the difference of measurements in inertial and accelerated reference systems. 
</para>
