<section id="section-4a">
<para id="element-27"><term>Problem 1 : </term> A pendulum is suspended from the roof of a train compartment, which is moving with a constant acceleration “a”. Find the deflection of the pendulum bob from the vertical as observed from the ground and the compartment. 
</para>
<para id="element-28"> <term>Solution : </term> We analyze the problem from the perspectives of both inertial and accelerated frames.
</para> 

<para id="element-29"><term>(i) </term> In the inertial frame of reference,
</para>
<para id="element-30">
<m:math>
<m:mtext> Free body diagram of pendulum bob </m:mtext>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-31">
The bob has acceleration “a” towards right. The forces on the bob are (i) weight of the bob, mg, and (ii) tension in the string.
</para>
<para id="element-32">
